{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2018}} {{Portuguese name|Dalot|Teixeira}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Diogo Dalot | image = | image_size = | caption = | fullname = José Diogo Dalot Teixeira<ref name=Soccerway/> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1999|3|18|df=y}}<ref name=Soccerway/> | birth_place = [[Braga]], Portugal | height = 1.84 m<ref name=Soccerway/> | position = [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|Full-back]] | currentclub = [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] | clubnumber = 20 | youthyears1 = 2008–2017 |youthclubs1 = [[FC Porto|Porto]] | years1 = 2017–2018 |clubs1 = [[FC Porto B|Porto B]] |caps1 = 23 |goals1 = 2 | years2 = 2017–2018 |clubs2 = [[FC Porto|Porto]] |caps2 = 6 |goals2 = 0 | years3 = 2018– |clubs3 = [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] |caps3 = 11 |goals3 = 0 | nationalyears1 = 2014 |nationalteam1 = Portugal U15 |nationalcaps1 = 2 |nationalgoals1 = 0 | nationalyears2 = 2014–2015 |nationalteam2 = [[Portugal national under-16 football team|Portugal U16]] |nationalcaps2 = 8 |nationalgoals2 = 0 | nationalyears3 = 2015–2016 |nationalteam3 = [[Portugal national under-17 football team|Portugal U17]] |nationalcaps3 = 19 |nationalgoals3 = 2 | nationalyears4 = 2016–2017 |nationalteam4 = [[Portugal national under-19 football team|Portugal U19]] |nationalcaps4 = 15 |nationalgoals4 = 0 | nationalyears5 = 2017– |nationalteam5 = [[Portugal national under-20 football team|Portugal U20]] |nationalcaps5 = 7 |nationalgoals5 = 0 | nationalyears6 = 2017– |nationalteam6 = [[Portugal national under-21 football team|Portugal U21]] |nationalcaps6 = 4 |nationalgoals6 = 0 | club-update = 19:07, 10 March 2019 (UTC) | nationalteam-update = 23:54, 29 May 2018 (UTC) | medaltemplates = {{Medal|Country|{{fb|Portugal}}}} {{MedalCompetition|[[UEFA European Under-17 Championship]]}} {{Medal|W|[[2016 UEFA European Under-17 Championship|Azerbaijan 2016]]|[[Portugal national under-17 football team|U-17 Team]]}} }} '''José Diogo Dalot Teixeira''' ({{IPA-pt|diˈoɡu dɐˈlo}};<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rtp.pt/noticias/futebol-internacional/diogo-dalot-a-caminho-do-manchester-united_v1078910 |title=Diogo Dalot a caminho do Manchester United |first=RTP, Rádio e Televisão de Portugal - |last=RTP |publisher=}}</ref> born 18 March 1999) is a Portuguese professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|full-back]] and occasional [[Winger (football)|winger]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://reddevilarmada.com/2019/03/03/manchester-united-found-new-right-winger-diogo-dalot/|title=Manchester United have found their new right winger – Diogo Dalot|date=2019-03-03|website=Red Devil Armada|language=en-US|access-date=2019-03-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/man-utd-news-diogo-dalot-15898611|title=Solskjaer explains Man United tactical change vs Crystal Palace|last=Luckhurst|first=Samuel|date=2019-02-28|website=men|access-date=2019-03-10}}</ref> for [[Premier League]] club [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]].
==Club career== ===Porto=== Born in [[Braga]], Dalot joined [[FC Porto|Porto]]'s youth system in 2008, aged nine.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.maisfutebol.iol.pt/p-s-para-seguir/nuno-travassos/dalot-o-vaivem-minhoto |title=Dalot, o vaivém minhoto|trans-title=Dalot, the whirlwind from Minho |publisher=Maisfutebol |language=Portuguese |last=Travassos |first=Nuno |date=3 June 2016 |accessdate=7 June 2017}}</ref> On 28 January 2017, he made his senior debut with [[FC Porto B|the B team]], playing the full 90 minutes in a 2–1 home loss against [[Leixões S.C.]] for the [[LigaPro]] championship.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fcporto.pt/pt/noticias/pages/fc-porto-b-leix%C3%B5es-24a-jornada-ledman-ligapro-1617.aspx |title="Bês" perdem na receção ao Leixões|trans-title=B's host Leixões and lose |publisher=FC Porto |language=Portuguese |date=28 January 2017 |accessdate=7 June 2017}}</ref>
Dalot first appeared with the first team in competitive games on 13 October 2017, starting in a 6–0 away win over [[Lusitano G.C.]] for [[2017–18 Taça de Portugal|the season]]'s [[Taça de Portugal]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/taca-de-portugal/artigos/analise-lusitano-0-6-fc-porto-como-gerires-o-teu-dragao |title=Análise Lusitano 0–6 FC Porto: Como gerires o teu 'dragão'|trans-title=Lusitano 0–6 FC Porto analysis: How to run one's 'dragon' |publisher=[[SAPO (company)|SAPO]] |language=Portuguese |date=14 October 2017 |accessdate=17 October 2017}}</ref> He first played in the [[Primeira Liga]] on 18 February 2018, coming on as a 75th-minute [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] in a 5–0 home routing of [[Rio Ave F.C.|Rio Ave FC]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.jn.pt/desporto/interior/f-c-porto-goleia-rio-ave-e-volta-a-lideranca-9128011.html |title=F. C. Porto goleia Rio Ave e volta à liderança|trans-title=F. C. Porto rout Rio Ave and reclaim first place |newspaper=[[Jornal de Notícias]] |language=Portuguese |date=18 February 2018 |accessdate=21 February 2018}}</ref>
===Manchester United=== Dalot signed for [[Premier League]] club [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] on 6 June 2018 on a five-year contract for a fee of £19&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44380881 |title=Diogo Dalot: Manchester United sign Porto right-back for £19m |first=Simon |last=Stone |publisher=BBC Sport |date=6 June 2018 |accessdate=6 June 2018}}</ref> He made his debut on 19 September 2018 in an away [[UEFA Champions League]] group stage match against Swiss side [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45578863 |title=Man Utd: Diogo Dalot could be at club for 10 years - Jose Mourinho |publisher=BBC Sport |date=19 September 2018}}</ref>
==International career== Dalot helped [[Portugal national under-17 football team|Portugal]] win the [[2016 UEFA European Under-17 Championship]], scoring twice in five games in Azerbaijan including once in the final against [[Spain national under-17 football team|Spain]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uefa.com/under17/season=2016/matches/round=2000595/match=2019912/index.html |title=Portugal win second U17 EURO title on penalties |publisher=UEFA |date=21 May 2016 |accessdate=7 June 2017}}</ref> [[2016 UEFA European Under-19 Championship|The same year]], he helped the [[Portugal national under-19 football team|under-19 team]] reach the quarter-finals of the same competition.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uefa.com/under19/season=2016/matches/round=2000599/match=2020325/index.html |title=Mbappé helps France past Portugal |publisher=UEFA |date=21 July 2016 |accessdate=7 June 2017}}</ref>
Dalot represented [[Portugal national under-20 football team|the nation]] at the [[2017 FIFA U-20 World Cup]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/news/y=2017/m=5/news=dalot-targeting-back-to-back-golden-summers-2886251.html |title=Dalot targeting back-to-back golden summers |publisher=FIFA |date=23 May 2017 |accessdate=7 June 2017}}</ref> starting in all the matches in an eventual quarter-final exit.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/matches/round=275956/match=300367044/match-report.html |title=Uruguay progress, Portugal pay the penalty |publisher=FIFA |date=4 June 2017 |accessdate=7 June 2017}}</ref>
